{
  "texts": [
    "This indicates that LMMs exhibit enhanced logical and mathematical reasoning abilities.As discussed earlier, the demonstrated logical and mathematical reasoning capabilities, evidenced by improved rationale measures, enable LMMs to map wireless observations and context information fed as input to them into a mathematical problem formulation.",
    "This empowers LMMs to function as dynamic problem solvers (defined in Section II-C3).",
    "To exemplify the application of these capabilities in future wireless systems, we next delve into a few use cases, including intent management and resilience.",
    "B. LMMs for Intent ManagementA recent work that exploits LLMs for intent management appeared in [3].",
    "However, this prior work is limited to using an LLM as a chatbot to convert human specified intent in natural language to infrastructure level intents as network service descriptors."
  ]
}